12/03/2022,748.455(a)(2) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,01/11/2023,01/11/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,No,The unauthorized debriefing did not include the trauma informed strategies a child can use to avoid future unauthorized absences and how the operation can support those strategies.  ,"As of 01/20/2023, the El Paso Center for Children will ensure that staff is trained on unauthorized absence-debrief trauma-informed strategies the child can use to avoid future unauthorized absences and how the operation can support strategies.  
1.)	Once a youth returns to the shelter from an unauthorized absence, the shelter staff will conduct a debriefing with the youth as soon as possible. The debriefing must be done no later than 24 hours after the child returns to the shelter. The following will be discussed with the youth.
a.	The circumstances that led to the childs unauthorized absence.
b.	The trauma-informed strategies the child can use to avoid future unauthorized absences and how the operation can support those strategies.
c.	The childs condition means their health and state of mind.
d.	What occurred while the child was away from the shelter, including:	
i.	Where the youth went.
ii.	Who was with the youth.
iii.	The youths activities.
iv.	Any other information that may be relevant to the childs health and safety. 
2.)	The shelter will allow the child to return to their routine activities, and will exclude any activity that the caregiver determines would be inappropriate because of the childs condition following the unauthorized absence or something that occurred during the unauthorized absence. 
3.)	The debriefing will be documented as a case note in the childs record, including any routine activity that would be inappropriate for the child to return to the shelter and the explanation for why the activity is inappropriate.
4.)	A template will be created for shelter staff to follow. 
"
