10/03/2022,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,11/28/2022,11/28/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,No,A staff member shut the door to the youth's room to call emergency services instead of assessing the youth for an injury.,"As of 12/16/2022, the El Paso Center for Children will ensure that staff is trained on prudent judgment, and self-control in the presence of children and when performing assigned responsibilities. 
1.)	Shelter staff will always carry with them a fanny pack that will have the shelters cell phone, cordless phone, shelter keys, and emergency numbers.
2.)	Having the phones on hand, staff can assess the youth and, in an emergency, can call for help. This will prevent the staff from leaving the youth unattended. 
"
10/02/2022,748.1003(a) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,10/31/2022,10/28/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,No,"On the day of the incident, the youth care worker was caring for 7 children alone. ","As of 10/20/2022, the El Paso Center for Children will ensure that staff is trained on the ratio of a single caregiver may care for five children if at least one child in the group requires treatment services, or eight children if none of the children in the group require treatment services. The shelter does not serve youth under 11, therefore children younger than five years old count as two children. Staff was trained on ratio on 10/22/2022.
1.)	The shelter will have two staff during the day and evening when there is a youth with treatment services. 
2.)	If the shelter has more than five youths and one has treatment services: if the staff has an emergency staff will not leave until the staff on call or another staff comes in to relieve the staff. 
"
07/28/2022,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,10/07/2022,10/05/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,Staff advised youths that were planning to run away to avoid using the windows to prevent property damage and use the main entrance instead. ,"As of 9/16/2022, the El Paso Center for Children will ensure that staff is trained on defining and demonstrating competency, prudent judgment, and self-control in the presence of children and when performing assigned tasks.
1.)	Staff will be trained on demonstrating competency, prudent judgment, and self-control on 09/23/2022.
2.)	Staff will talk to the youth once they know youth are planning to leave the shelter.
3.)	Staff will let the youth know that it is not safe to leave the shelter. A shelter is a safe place with food, water, and shelter. 
4.)	Staff will contact the youth's CPS worker or legal guardian to inform them about the youth's plans. Try to have them talk to the youth. 
"
