06/08/2021,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/05/2021,08/04/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,No,,"As of 8/5/2021, the El Paso Center for Children will ensure that staff is trained on defining and demonstrating competency, prudent judgment, self-control in the presence of children and when performing assigned tasks.
1.)	As of 05/26/2021, Mr. Finlayson was not left alone during his shift. A second staff member was added to the night shift to work with Mr. Finlayson. 
2.)	Staff will be trained on demonstrating competency, prudent judgment, and self-control on 8/10/2021.
3.)	The Program Director will conduct random camera checks weekly to ensure the safety of the youth. 
4.)	Ms. Lorena Calvillos investigation focused on potential lack of prudent judgment.   Based on the exit interview with Ms. Calvillo found that  Mr. Finlayson did not show prudent judgment and self-control in the presence of the youth in his care and required that a corrective action plan be submitted by the agency by 8/05/2021. Based on these findings, the relationship between El Paso Center for Children and Mr. Finlayson has been terminated. "
